==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Shoad
<hw>Shoad</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. G.
<ets>schutt</ets> rubbish.]</ety> <fld>(Mining)</fld> <def>A train of
vein material mixed with rubbish; fragments of ore which have become
separated by the action of water or the weather, and serve to direct in
the discovery of mines.</def> <altsp>[Written also
<asp>shode</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Shoading</ent>⟦br⟧
